    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-14T20:00:00-05:00" n="494"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.516/143: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 14, 1932—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Department’s telegram No. 35, June 14, 6 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d494fn13"
                        >Not printed; in it the Department requested text of the official statement
                        of the Minister of Hacienda concerning operation of the Central Bank.</note>
                    “Minister of Hacienda has declared officially that, in accordance with the
                    decree laws promulgated recently with respect to the organization of the State
                    Bank, the Central Bank of Chile shall continue as before to be governed by its
                    own laws and statutes performing the same functions which it had by virtue of
                    its organic law. Its resources (<hi rend="italic">patrimonio</hi>) shall
                    continue independent of fiscal resources and also of the resources of the State
                    Bank, and shall not be confused with them.”</p>
                <p>The decree laws referred to in the first sentence of the foregoing statement are,
                    as far as can be ascertained, those mentioned in my telegram 89, June 14, 5
                    p.m., but they have not been promulgated as stated by the Minister of
                    Hacienda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
